#: ../../B/bletcherous.rst:5
msgid "bletcherous"
msgstr "bletcherous"

#: ../../B/bletcherous.rst:7
msgid "/blech'\\@·r\\@s/, adj\\."
msgstr "/blech'\\@·r\\@s/, 形容詞"

#: ../../B/bletcherous.rst:9
msgid ""
"Disgusting in design or function; esthetically unappealing. This word is "
"seldom used of people. \"This keyboard is bletcherous!\" (Perhaps the keys "
"don't work very well, or are misplaced.) See :ref:`losing`\\, "
":ref:`cretinous`\\, :ref:`bagbiting`\\, :ref:`bogus`\\, and :ref:`random`\\."
" The term :ref:`bletcherous` applies to the esthetics of the thing so "
"described; similarly for :ref:`cretinous`\\. By contrast, something that is "
"losing or bagbiting may be failing to meet objective criteria. See also "
":ref:`bogus` and :ref:`random`\\, which have richer and wider shades of "
"meaning than any of the above."
msgstr ""
"設計や機能が胸の悪くなるような、美的に魅力のない。この語が人に使われることはめったにない。「このキーボードはbletcherousだ!」(おそらくキーがうまく動かないか、配置が悪いのだ)。\\"
" :ref:`losing`\\ 、\\ :ref:`cretinous`\\ 、\\ :ref:`bagbiting`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`bogus`\\ 、\\ :ref:`random`\\ を参照。\\ :ref:`bletcherous`\\ "
"という用語は、そう表現されるものの美的側面に当てはまる。\\ :ref:`cretinous`\\ "
"も同様。対照的に、losingやbagbitingなものは、客観的な基準を満たし損ねているのかもしれない。上記のいずれよりも豊かで広い意味合いを持つ\\"
" :ref:`bogus`\\ と\\ :ref:`random`\\ も参照。"
